04/03/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Talks on forming a new government are expected to continue among parties in the democratic bloc this week, according to a statement Saturday (March 3rd) from President Boris Tadic's Democratic Party (DS). In the first round of negotiations last week, with the Democratic Party of Serbia (DSS)-New Serbia (NS) coalition, the two sides discussed political priorities, such as preserving Kosovo and Metohija within Serbia's borders, accelerating the country's EU integration process, full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, boosting economic development and fighting corruption and crime. DS plans talks Monday with G17 Plus. (RTS, Blic, Tanjug - 03/03/07)
